OL,5,CMinister
OL,7,FAlliance deputy leader Eoin Tennyson
OL,8,Fsaid any department facing an over-
OL,9,Fcommitment should not be diverting
OL,10,Fcash to expenditure that was
OL,11,Fdiscretionary.
OL,13,FMs Archibald replied: "I do agree with
OL,14,Fthe member that addressing over-
OL,15,Fcommitments should be the top priority
OL,16,Ffor any minister and living within
OL,17,Ftheir budget.
